review_blob: Bottle from systemet Hagfors. Clear Amber, white head that doesnt stay. OK IPA, but probably lost a lot of its hop flavour.
Bottle from System Bolaget Karlstad Bergvik. Pours deep yellow with medium head. Strong IPA, grapefruit aroma. Sweet and sour taste... Wow!
Bottle from liquor store, Av Princessa, Barcelona. Aroma somewhat bandaid, golden brown, head doesnt stay. OK taste, somewhat hoppy, slightly salted as promised
Bottle from Mercat, Barceloneta. Citrus aroma. Pours a cloudy golden ale, head doesnt stay. OK sweet and sour taste, sticky mouth feel, lemonade.
Bottle from Mercat Barceloneta. Hoppy aroma, pours a light, clean APA with a white thick head. Tastes a little watery/soapy though. Pretty malty.
Bottle from Metcat Barceloneta. Hoppy aroma. Pours a clean light APA, with a thick white head. Tastes a little watery / soapy though.
@Westerpark, thanks to our. Hop flavor has worn a little a off. But still a very nice IPA. Sticky mouthfeel .
beer_name: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: @westerpark, thanks to jur. Good mouth feel, straight, clean blipa. Pours a nice head.
@Westerpark, flown in by jur, wow! Great red colour , awesome hoppy taste. Little sticky aftertaste.
Bottle from C1000, nice beer but a little too much orange for my taste. Could use some more hops.
At Arendsnest, Amsterdam. Nice copper color, white head, hoppy flavor with good aroma.
At arendsnest, amsterdam. Nice colour thin white head. Ok pale ale, little heavy aroma, berry flavour, could be a somewhat more crisp for my taste.
Bottle from Spar Spaardammerstraat. Nice color and fine head. The hippy taste is excellent, especially for the low ABV!
Bottle from Spar Spaarndammerstraat. Nice dark colour, slightly beige head. Little dull Blipa though, not that hoppy,sour aftertaste.
Bottle from systembolaget Bergvik, Karlstad. Nice dark yellow, white head. Really surprising aroma and taste. Lychee, vanilla.
Bottle from systembolaget Bergvik, Karlstad. Copper Pale Ale, ok white head. Aroma and taste are somewhat flat. Ok craft beer.
Bottle from systembolaget Bergvik, Karlstad. Nice copper colour, good white head. Heavy, but very drinkable considering the ABV. Hints of cherry.
From systembolaget Karlstad, light copper, small head, very nice and fresh hoppy aroma (grass), piny, resin. Impressive for only 4.6 abv.
From Systembolaget in Hagfors. Light colored Ale, hardly any head, low carbonation. Taste is ok, celeia proves to be a nice hop, but as with many (s)mash ales, not very complex.
Bottle from Systembolaget Hagfors. Pours copper, great IPA, good aroma and bittering hops.
Bottle from Systembolaget Hagfors. Just a good Pale Ale, Cascade gives a nice citrus aroma.
Ok but standard IPA, nice color, good aroma from the Amarillo and Centennial. Little watery though.
